#compdef jsdiff
# ============================================================================
# jsdiff - character-grained two-file diff with ANSI
#           color output (JavaScript -> Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Kalpesh Adhatrao (kelsadita)
# Upstream: https://github.com/kelsadita/jsdiff-cli
# npm    : jsdiff-cli (binary: jsdiff)
#
# `jsdiff` is a minimal CLI for getting a character-
# level diff between two text files. The output is
# colored ANSI:
#   - green for inserted characters
#   - red for deleted characters
#   - grey for unchanged characters
# Output is written to stderr (so the colored stream
# can coexist with shell pipelines that consume
# stdout for other purposes).
#
# Usage:
#   jsdiff <file1> <file2>
#
# Args:
#   <file1>     - original file
#   <file2>     - modified file
#
# There are no flags - jsdiff is intentionally
# minimal. For richer diff output (unified diff,
# side-by-side, word-level), pair the underlying
# `diff` npm package (kpdecker/jsdiff) directly in
# a Node script + customize the output formatting.
#
# Operational model:
#   1. Read both files into memory
#   2. Call `jsdiff.diffChars(data1, data2)` (kpdecker/
#      jsdiff's character-grained Myers diff)
#   3. Walk the resulting parts array + emit per-
#      part ANSI-colored output to stderr
#
# The kpdecker/jsdiff lane is built on `diff ~1.0.7`
# (declared at upstream package.json HEAD as a direct
# dep, imported as `require("diff")` then named
# `jsdiff` in the binary), the canonical Node diff
# library by Kevin Decker (kpdecker) - github.com/
# kpdecker/jsdiff, 3500+ stars, ~50M weekly npm
# downloads.
#
# kpdecker/jsdiff is a *pure-JS reimplementation* of
# Myers diff + LCS-based diff variants in idiomatic
# JavaScript. The library exposes per-granularity
# entry points:
#   - diffChars(a, b)        - character-level diff
#   - diffWords(a, b)        - word-level diff
#                              (whitespace + word
#                              boundary aware)
#   - diffWordsWithSpace(a,b)- word-level diff with
#                              spaces preserved
#   - diffLines(a, b)        - line-level diff
#   - diffTrimmedLines(a,b)  - line-level diff with
#                              trailing-space tolerance
#   - diffSentences(a, b)    - sentence-level diff
#   - diffCss(a, b)          - CSS-aware diff (token-
#                              boundary aware)
#   - diffJson(a, b)         - JSON-structural diff
#   - diffArrays(a, b)       - array-element diff
#
# The library is one of the most-depended-on packages
# in the npm ecosystem (top 200 by reverse-
# dependencies, alongside lodash + chalk + axios).
# Direct or transitive dependents include:
#   - Jest (test framework's assertion library)
#   - Mocha (test framework)
#   - Chai (assertion library)
#   - Storybook (component diff for storyshots)
#   - Prettier (--check output formatting)
#   - GitHub's diff renderer (via
#     react-diff-viewer-continued)
#   - VS Code's text diff peek view
#   - ESLint's autofix diff display
#
# jsdiff (THIS BINARY) uses the `diffChars` variant
# specifically because character-level output gives
# the most fine-grained visual diff - typos and
# casing changes that line-level diff would smear
# across the whole line are isolated to the
# individual character changes.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 252 :: Diffing libraries (Myers / Patience /
#              LCS algorithms with multi-format output)
# Round 1456 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 252
#                                       (245th axis closed)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : mitsuhiko/similar           [R1454 _mdslw]
#   Go      : sergi/go-diff               [R1455 _gofmtmd]
#   TS/Node : kpdecker/jsdiff             [R1456 THIS FILE]
#             (npm `diff` package)
#
# kpdecker/jsdiff closes Axis 252 with the *pure-JS-
# reimplementation-with-multi-granularity-API*
# pattern. The three lanes form a clean spectrum:
#
#   - Rust (mitsuhiko/similar): multi-algorithm
#     Rust implementation (Myers + Patience + LCS +
#     Histogram); high-level output adapters (unified
#     diff + side-by-side + character-grained inline);
#     depended on by insta + cargo-insta + difftastic
#     + rustfmt's --check output
#   - Go (sergi/go-diff): line-by-line port of
#     Google's diff-match-patch C++ library; preserves
#     upstream API + benefits from Google's
#     maintenance; depended on by Terraform + kubectl
#     + most Go infrastructure tools that output
#     diffs
#   - Node (kpdecker/jsdiff): pure-JS reimplementation
#     by Kevin Decker; multi-granularity API
#     (diffChars + diffWords + diffLines +
#     diffSentences + diffCss + diffJson + diffArrays);
#     top-200 npm package by reverse-dependency
#     count; depended on by Jest + Mocha + Chai +
#     Storybook + Prettier + VS Code
#
# Cross-language interop happens at the diff-structure
# level - same input produces same set of insertions /
# deletions / equal segments across all three lanes
# (modulo equivalent algorithmic choices). Output
# formatting differs:
#   - similar: unified + side-by-side + inline
#   - go-diff: patch + match + diff operation triple
#   - jsdiff: per-granularity diffChars / diffWords /
#     diffLines / ... entry points
# All three can convert between formats via their
# adapter functions.
#
# Use-case spectrum across the three lanes:
#   - mdslw (Rust, similar): markdown semantic line-
#     wrapper using Myers diff for --report diff
#     output
#   - gofmtmd (Go, sergi/go-diff): gofmt applied to
#     Go code blocks in markdown, using sergi/go-diff
#     to minimize per-block edits
#   - jsdiff (Node, kpdecker/jsdiff): character-
#     grained two-file diff CLI with ANSI color
#     output, using diffChars directly
#
# Three lanes, three use-case shapes (markdown
# rewrapper / code-block formatter / file diff CLI),
# three implementation strategies (re-derive from
# papers / port Google reference / pure-JS
# reimplementation), all converging on Myers-
# algorithm structural equivalence.
#
# Axis 252 closes the round 1456 cycle - 245th axis
# closed total.
# ============================================================================

_jsdiff() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '1:original file:_files' \
        '2:modified file:_files'
}

_jsdiff "$@"
